Class EventManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.kushnirvladyslav.EventManager

  • public class EventManager
extends Object
    Central event management system that implements the Singleton pattern. Handles event publishing, subscription, and dispatching to registered subscribers. Thread-safe implementation using CopyOnWriteArrayList for subscribers and PriorityBlockingQueue for event queue.

    The EventManager supports the following lifecycle states:

    • CREATED - Initial state after instantiation
    • RUNNING - Active event processing
    • PAUSED - Temporarily stopped, can be resumed
    • STOPPED - Stopped, can be restarted
    • SHUTDOWN - Permanently disabled
    Since:
    2025-06-11
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Vladyslav Kushnir
